column2: Partly cloudy- rain storm this morning- loon family visible.
Partly cloudy- moderately windy- pickerel weed blooming.
Sunny- very breezy- pickerel weed still blooming.
Partly cloudy- windy- blue flag blooming.  2 loons swimming near canoe.  75 F.
Light breeze- calm water- 72 F.  Pickerel weed blooming.
Partly cloudy- calm- 82 F.  Loon parent.  Juvinile diving.
Hazy- mostly cloudy.  Lake very calm (no loons).
Sunny- many cumulus clouds- 10 mph breeze.
72 F- beautiful day.  Light breeze.  Pickerel weed blooming.
78F Partly cloudy- breezy- no loons today- chicks lost to predation (presumably)
58 F- Sunny- clear.  Wind is calm.
cloudy with a slight breeze- two loons spotted
partly cloudy with slight  breeze. 4 loons spotted; 2 of them were babies
Partly cloudy with slight breeze.  One juvenile loon.
Cloudy- windy- 72 F.  Saw 2 loons and 1 blue heron.
Sunny- breezy.  Saw 1 adult and 1 baby loon.
Partly cloudy- breezy- 52 F.  2 adult loons dancing on water.
Mostly cloudy- light breeze.  Ice out was 3 weeks ago to date.  Unable to get out sooner for sampling....best we could do.  Heidi Magayne helped out husband Jerry for testing.
overcast 60 F air temp.  Slight breeze.
sunny- slight breeze.  Saw one adult loon- and one buck on the island (injured rear leg).
Partly sunny with a mild breeze.  Temp around high 40's.
Sunny day with high altitude clouds and it was breezy.
saw one loon. Overcast and calm.

column1: one deer on shore drinking out of lake

column2: sunny- windy- slight chop on water- saw 2 loons
Sunny brisk day with a slight breeze.  No clouds.  Saw 1 loon and 1 mallard duck.
Sunny and breezy.  Assisted by John Ciesielski.  Observed one eagle flying over the lake.  No Loons. Sunny and Breezy.  About 78 degrees. Observed one eagle.  No Loons.
Sunny with a slight breeze- 82 degrees
2 loons with growing baby.  Wind kicking up - made temp. readings challenging.
Partly cloudy- light breeze.  2 very quiet loons.  1 muskrat swimming the shore.
Clear sky- light breeze. Saw 2 loons 10 feet away from testing area. 78 degrees.
Windy and partly cloudy.  First sight of the loon on the west end of the lake.  She called out to us.  Ice came off the lake on 4/11/15.
Light to medium breeze. Partly cloudy.  Saw 2 loons in the water and 1 duck flying overhead. Ice off 4/13/16.
Ice off 4/9/17 and Loons were back same day.  Today partly cloudy and breezy.  Saw one loon by the island.
Heidi Magayne was the other field tester on this excursion.  Water level at it's highest.   Island submerged.  Cloudy and breezy.
Cloudy- some breeze intermittently- loon out on water.
Quite windy- clear blue sky.  Air temperature is 64.5.
Partly cloudy- windy- no waterfowl- 1 eagle
with John Brunette.  Calm- sunny.  One loon- one family of ducks.
Blue sky- sunny- breezy- no water fowl- 1 eagle.
